Arkadian LMS (ALMS) — Continuing Development (Session 15)

I'm building Arkadian LMS, a Learning Management System for ARK Technological Institute Education System Inc. Picking up from Session 14. There is also a parallel AI integration track running in separate sessions — see the dedicated section below.

🎯 What was completed in Session 14

Four queue items shipped, all tested and confirmed working in-browser.

Item 1: Personal task improvements ✅ SHIPPED

Completed the work deferred from Session 12. No migration needed — personal_tasks already had every column (completed_at, updated_at, the right partial indexes).

- src/lib/actions/personalTasks.ts — added updatePersonalTask(taskId, patch) (patch-style; `'dueAt' in patch` semantics so an explicit null clears the date, omitting it leaves it alone) and listMyCompletedPersonalTasks(limit=50) (sorted completed_at desc). listMyActivePersonalTasks now also selects completed_at. markPersonalTaskUndone already existed from Session 13 and is now actually wired to UI.
- src/components/dashboard/PersonalTasksPanel.tsx — full rewrite. Active/Completed filter pills (Completed view fetches on-demand the first time it's opened — the parent to-do widgets only pass active items, so completed tasks are NOT eager-loaded). Edit-in-place via a pencil icon (title, due date with a Clear button, notes; Escape cancels; ISO→local-input conversion handled). Expandable rows show full notes — the old 8rem truncation is gone. Completed rows: strikethrough title, "completed Xh ago", Restore button (markPersonalTaskUndone), Delete-forever.
- src/lib/types/dashboard.ts — added `completedAt: string | null` to PersonalTaskItem.

Recurring tasks were deliberately NOT done — bigger lift, still deferred.

Item 2: Activity duplicate / "Copy from another class" ✅ SHIPPED

No migration — everything fit existing schema. Storage attachments are deep-copied (independent classes; storage cost accepted).

- src/lib/actions/activities.ts — three new actions: listTeacherClassesForCopy(), listClassActivitiesForCopy(classId), and duplicateActivity({sourceActivityId, targetClassId, targetTerm}). Also a bonus fix: deleteActivity was leaking activity_attachment storage objects on delete (RLS cascade kills DB rows but not storage) — added the cleanup loop.
- duplicateActivity behavior: copies title (with "(copy)" suffix only on same-class duplicates; cross-class keeps original title), instructions, prompt, activity_kind, max_points, submission_type, allow_late, allow_resubmission, all quiz settings (time_limit_minutes, shuffle_questions, auto_release_grade, show_correct_answers, quiz_total_points), all quiz_questions with config jsonb intact, all activity_attachments. Resets: published→false, start_at→now(), due_at→now()+7d, display_order→end of target term. Never copies submissions/attempts/responses/grades.
- Atomicity: insert activity → insert questions → storage.copy() each attachment + insert attachment rows. On any failure: remove already-copied storage objects, delete the new activity (FK cascade cleans questions + attachment rows), rethrow. Uses Supabase Storage server-side copy() (no download/reupload). Storage path scheme mirrors existing convention: `<target_class_id>/<new_uuid>/<timestamp>-<safe_filename>`.
- quiz_total_points and max_points are copied directly from source (no recompute needed). Quiz duplication does NOT call assertNotLocked — locking guards editing the source, not reading it to copy.
- src/components/teacher/CopyFromClassModal.tsx — NEW. 3-step picker: pick source class → pick source activity → pick target term (defaults to source's term). Calls duplicateActivity, navigates to the new activity's editor.
- src/components/teacher/ActivitiesTab.tsx — full rewrite. Inline Copy icon on each activity card (same-class duplicate → navigates to editor). Top-level "Copy from another class" button next to AddActivityBar → opens the modal.

Item 3: Admin dashboard audit ✅ SHIPPED (Tier 1 + Tier 2 read-only)

