📋 Important contracts and gotchas (cumulative + new)

All Session 4–13 constraints still apply, plus everything from "Bugs found" above, plus these:

- profiles has NO self-service UPDATE RLS policy. A user CANNOT update their own profile row directly through the RLS'd client. last_active_at is updated via the touch_last_active() SECURITY DEFINER RPC. If a future feature needs a user to edit their own profile (e.g. change display name, avatar), it needs EITHER a carefully column-scoped approach (SECURITY DEFINER RPC per field, or an UPDATE policy + a BEFORE UPDATE trigger that rejects changes to role/email/calendar_token) — NOT a blanket "users can update their own profile" policy. That policy would be a privilege-escalation hole because RLS can't restrict columns.
- touch_last_active() is the ONLY current SECURITY DEFINER write-path outside of pre-existing RPCs. It only ever sets last_active_at for auth.uid(). Don't extend it to touch other columns — if you need more, write a separate scoped function.
- last_active_at update is unthrottled. Every protected-route navigation by any authenticated user fires touch_last_active(). This also bumps profiles.updated_at via the existing trigger on every navigation — harmless (updated_at isn't load-bearing) but be aware. If write volume ever becomes a concern (it won't at this scale), add an interval check INSIDE the SQL function, not in the PostgREST client.
- last_active_at tracked for ALL roles, displayed only for students. The middleware updates it for admin/teacher/student alike; only StudentsTab renders it. The data is there if you ever want "last active" on the admin teacher list etc.
- Never put a raw ISO timestamp inside a PostgREST .or() / .filter() string. The `:` chars break the parser silently. Timestamp comparisons go in SQL.
- duplicateActivity uses Supabase Storage copy() (server-side, no download/reupload). Storage path scheme for any new activity-attachment work: `<class_id>/<uuid>/<timestamp>-<safe_filename>` where safe_filename is `file_name.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9._-]/g, '_')`.
- deleteActivity now also cleans up activity_attachments storage objects (was leaking them — RLS cascade only kills DB rows). If you add another path that deletes activities, mirror this.
- Admin pages assume the caller is admin. middleware.ts gates /admin/* by role AND admin/layout.tsx re-checks. admin.ts actions don't re-check role (rely on those two layers + RLS). Keep that invariant — don't add an /admin/* page that does its own un-gated data fetch.
- admin/sections/page.tsx is still a stub. Deferred by user decision. The /admin/* guard still protects it.
- The Session 13 contracts all still hold: SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY required (calendar .ics route only), notifications insert policy is permissive, notify* inserters swallow errors, useServerSyncedState is list/object-prop-sync ONLY (not for ActivityEditor/QuizEditor paired-draft pattern), xlsx-js-style NOT xlsx for exports, calendar fetch contract uses getStudentCalendarItems/getTeacherCalendarItems.

MANDATORY pre-migration drift check (run at the start of ANY session that will write a migration):
```
ls supabase/migrations/ | tail -5
docker exec -i $(docker ps -q -f name=supabase_db) psql -U postgres -d postgres -c "SELECT version FROM supabase_migrations.schema_migrations ORDER BY version DESC LIMIT 5;"
```
The file list and tracker rows must match. If a file exists on disk but not in the tracker (AI-track drift), diagnose first:
- Check whether the migration's effect is already in the DB (e.g. `\d <table>` for the column it adds).
- If YES (effect present, tracker row missing) → manual repair, then `supabase migration up`:
  ```
  INSERT INTO supabase_migrations.schema_migrations (version, name, statements)
  VALUES ('<timestamp>', '<name>', ARRAY['-- manually marked applied'])
  ON CONFLICT (version) DO NOTHING;
  ```
- If NO (effect genuinely missing) → `supabase migration up --include-all` is appropriate.
Never run --include-all blindly without checking which case you're in.

